This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper specifically focuses on the partially cooperative relay broadcast channel, which involves networked communication and falls under cs.NI. The use of side information is a key aspect of the paper, which makes it relevant to cs.SI. The paper also mentions the use of dirty paper coding, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia communication and falls under cs.MM. Finally, the paper discusses the use of random parameters, which can be relevant to computer engineering and falls under cs.CE.
